{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VKDUMgKEYYTRuRuL7cQjXE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS is working. The curl exits with code 0 and the response is `hello`.\n\n**What was wrong:** The `demo-ingress` Ingress was referencing `expired-tls-secret`, which held a TLS certificate that expired on 2020-01-02 — over 6 years ago.\n\n**What I did:**\n1. Located the Test CA private key at `/tmp/test-ca.kc-karma-6.key` (generated by the precondition setup on the host)\n2. Generated a new 10-year leaf cert for `demo.example.com` with the correct SAN, signed by the Test CA\n3. Created a new secret `demo-tls-secret` with the valid cert/key\n4. Patched `demo-ingress` to reference `demo-tls-secret` instead of `expired-tls-secret`\n\nThe TLS handshake now completes successfully — `SSL certificate verify ok`, cert issued by `CN=Test CA`, valid 2026–2036, and the backend returns `hello` with HTTP 200."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1359,"cache_read_input_tokens":52330,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1359},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbc7f87c-46aa-448c-a606-8f0806857b3e","uuid":"a51a83d3-25a0-434a-8911-a087c54e23cd","request_id":"req_011CcekpGN9AhbWsdUgc4sxY"}
